Package awesoma.common.commands

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ExecutAble
    interface represents command execution cycle
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Add
    This command adds an element with given fields to the collection
    AddIfMax
    Adds an element in the collection if its totalBoxOffice value is maximum in the collection
    Clear
    this command clears the collection
    Command
    Abstract class that represents command being
    ExecuteScript
    this command executes script from the file string by string
    Exit
    this command closes the program without saving the collection to file
    Help
    this commands shows name and description of registered commands
    Info
    this command shows info about current collection like amount od elements, initialization date and etc
    PrintFieldAscendingTotalBoxOffice
    this command prints totalBoxOffice values of collection elements in ascending order
    PrintFieldDescendingGenre
    this command prints genre values of collection elements in descending order
    PrintFieldDescendingUsaBoxOffice
    this command prints usaBoxOffice values of collection elements in descending order
    Quit
    this command closes the program without saving the collection to file, same as Exit command just by 'q'
    RemoveAt
    This command removes element from the collection by given index
    RemoveById
    This command deletes an element with given id from the collection
    Save
    This command saves collection to the file which stated in env path
    Show
    This commands shows elements of the collection
    Sort
    This command sorts the collection by Movie.id
    UpdateId
    This command updates an element with given id
